Prerequisite: 

1. Installed python 3.X.X

2. Installed Virtual Environment
    > pip install virtualenv

Step 1: Create a Virtual Environment
        Syntax: virtualenv --distribute nameodenvironment --python=python_version    
        Example: virtualenv --distribute env --python=python
Step 2: Activate the Created virtual Environment
        source env/bin/activate

Step 2: Install Django
        pip install Django

Step 3: Create Django Project
        django-admin startproject web_project .

Step 4: Testing Django
        python manage.py runserver
        or
        python manage.py runserver 8001

Step 5: To create Django app
        python manage.py startapp app

Step 6: Swagger Install
        Ref: https://django-rest-swagger.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
        Error Resolve: Put the below line in settings.py 
        REST_FRAMEWORK = { 'DEFAULT_SCHEMA_CLASS': 'rest_framework.schemas.coreapi.AutoSchema' }